content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and block dictionary to provide a precise solution:

Target Structure Analysis:
- Two separate block structures
- Structure 1 (Left):
  * 3 layers high
  * Bottom layer: Yellow rectangular base, two orange cylindrical blocks
  * Middle layer: Yellow rectangular block
  * Top layer: Blue rectangular block, red rectangular block, orange triangular roof block

- Structure 2 (Right):
  * 3 layers high
  * Bottom layer: Red arch/curved block
  * Middle layer: Yellow rectangular block
  * Top layer: Red rectangular block, orange triangular roof block

Block Selection from Dictionary:
1. Bottom layer Structure 1: Blocks 9 (yellow rectangle), 11 & 12 (orange cylinders)
2. Bottom layer Structure 2: Block 1 (red arch)
3. Middle layer for both: Block 10 (yellow rectangle)
4. Top layer Structure 1: Block 7 (blue cube), Block 6 (red cube), Block 16 (orange triangle)
5. Top layer Structure 2: Block 6 (red cube), Block 16 (orange triangle)

Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block 9 (yellow rectangle)
    Step2: Move blocks 11 and 12 (orange cylinders)
    Step3: Move block 1 (red arch)
    Step4: Move block 10 (yellow rectangle) on top of bottom layers
    Step5: Move block 7 (blue cube)
    Step6: Move block 6 (red cube)
    Step7: Move block 16 (orange triangle) on top of Structure 1
    Step8: Move block 6 (red cube) on Structure 2
    Step9: Move block 16 (orange triangle) on top of Structure 2
}
